title: Elks rout Coyotes 41-0
text:
Elks rout Coyotes 41-0 0 comments 
EAGAR â€” The Round Valley Elks rolled for 569 yards of total offense in a 41-0 victory against visiting Phoenix Arizona Lutheran in a Division 5 football game on Friday, Sept. 25. 
Sullivan Udall led the Elks with 18 carries for 163 yards and three touchdowns. Kyron Woolf, who was six-of-10 passing for 163 yards, ran five times for 146 yards and two scores. Bryson Brown ran seven times for 60 yards as Round Valley gained 386 yards on the ground. 
The Elks put up gaudy offensive numbers while the defense had three takeaways in posting the shutout. Woolf averaged 29.2 yards per rush. Clayton Merrill led the Elks with 67 yards on two catches and he also had an interception which he returned for 30 yards. 
Rodney Emerald had 130 yards in punt returns. Oscar Cortez led the defense with 13 tackles while Udall and Dillon Workman had 10 stops apiece. Cortez and Workman each had a fumble recovery. 
The Coyotes dropped to 2-3 with the loss. 
Tonight the Elks (3-2) host the Alchesay Falcons (1-4) in a 7 p.m. game.
